Quote Favorites Web App
This is a web application that allows users to search for famous quotes by authors and save their favorite quotes to view later.

Technologies Used
Node.js: A JavaScript runtime environment for executing server-side code.
Express.js: A web application framework for Node.js.
MySQL: A relational database management system used to store favorite quotes.
Bootstrap 5: A front-end framework for building responsive and mobile-first websites.
Git: A distributed version control system for tracking changes to code.
Installation
Clone the repository to your local machine:

bash

git clone https://github.com/your-username/quote-favorites-web-app.git
Install dependencies:

bash

cd quote-favorites-web-app
npm install
Set up the MySQL database:

Create a MySQL database named quotes.
Update the database configuration in config/dbConfig.js with your MySQL username and password.
Start the server:


node server.js
Open your web browser and navigate to http://localhost:3000/ to access the application.

Usage
Search Page: Enter keywords to search for quotes by authors. Click on the favorite button to save a quote to your favorites.
Favorites Page: View all your saved favorite quotes.
Directory Structure
arduino

